{
  "$schema": "./visual-claims.schema.md",
  "description": "Task-6 visual-claims manifest for the keybinding manager QA. Task 6 renders no styled TUI of its own (it is the key-resolution engine consumed by later tasks), so its single visual claim is the tmux-captured qaharness run in session ulw-qa-t6: driving the scripted keys shift+tab / ctrl+o / ctrl+r (as both raw sequences and bubbletea KeyPressMsg), the ctrl+p scope split, an override flip, and the malformed-keybindings.json failure fallback, then asserting the resulting PASS/VERDICT lines against the parsed cell grid. The .ans is a real `tmux capture-pane -p` of the ulw-qa-t6 pane, CRLF-normalized so the xterm-headless harness applies the same ONLCR newline semantics the live cooked-mode terminal did (the harness parser does not apply ONLCR to bare \\n; the pane content itself is left-aligned and uncolored). verify-manifest re-runs these grid assertions against the on-disk JSON so the manifest cannot lie. Triplet paths are relative to this manifest's directory (packages/neo/qa).",
